https://guides.github.com/introduction/git-handbook/
Install Git:

1. Install Git from https://git-scm.com/downloads.

2. Confirm the CLI is properly installed by running the following command. : git --version


Configure Your Git Identity:

1. Set your name to associate as the author of future Git commits. This should be your first and/or last name.

	git config --global user.name "Your Name"
	
2. Set your email address to associate as the author of future Git commits. This should be the email address you use with GitHub.

	git config --global user.email "you@email.com"
	
Create a Local Git Repository:

1. initialize a local Git repository

	git init
	
2. check .gitignore  save the below contents into the file.
	
	.sfdx
	.vscode
	.DS_Store
	
Commit Your Files to Git :

1. git add .

2. git commit --message "Initial commit of DreamHouse metadata"

Push Your Files to GitHub:

1. Link your local Git repository with your remote GitHub repository. Make sure to replace YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME with your actual GitHub username.

	git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME/sfdx-project.git
	
2. Push local commits (your file revisions) to the master branch on GitHub.
	
	git push origin master
	

create a feature branch locally in VS code:

1. git checkout -b faeture/COES-3633

